cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CY, cs.HC 

The paper proposes a parametric framework for the multi-armed bandit problem that incorporates reward processing biases associated with several neurological and psychiatric conditions. This suggests that the paper could be relevant to several sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), cybernetics (cs.CY), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Among these, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories as the paper proposes a new approach for solving a machine learning problem.
